    <h1 style="text-align: center;color: green;font-size: 50px;"> SULLAMUSALAM SCIENCE COLLEGE</h1>
    <p style="text-align: right;">
    <center></centre><img style="width: 800px; ;height: 400px; "src="yb.jpeg" alt=""></center>
       <br><p style="font-size:30px ;"> Sullamussalam Science College is a first grade aided college affiliated to University of Calicut, approved by University Grants Commission and accredited by the NAAC with A grade. The College is located on the picturesque hills of Perumparamba on the banks of the river Chaliyar, a kilometer away from Areacode town in Malappuram District. The college is run by Muslim Educational Association, an educational organization formed in 1994 under the auspices of Jamiyyathul Mujahideen Sangam, one of the pioneer reformist muslim educational movements in Malabar. The college was founded with the objective of imparting quality education to backward minority communities in rural areas of Malabar. Thanks to the Almighty, it has so far triumphed in its objectives, despite various constraints.&nbsp; Now on a stable footing, the college is venturing into new avenues of higher education. Policies&nbsp;and Special features The management believes in Islamic values and in the true spirit of education and thus totally against the commercialization of education. No capitation fee for staff appointments and student admissions Consistently excellent academic records Many prestigious University ranks No politics based elections The campus is free from strikes Exemplary student democratic activities Many clubs and forums meant for all-round development of students</p>
    <br><h2 style="text-align: center;text-transform: uppercase;">Departments</h2><br>
<h3 style="text-transform: uppercase;margin-left: 30px;color: rgb(153, 17, 17);">Computer Science</h3>
<center></centre><img style="width: 600px; ;height: 300px; "src="cs.jpeg" alt=""></center>
<p style="font-size:20px ;">The Department has been functioning since the inception of the college in 1995. One of the largest computer science departments under the University of Calicut, the PG Course was started in 2001, with10 seats. The department has a pass percentage of 100 in almost all the years. Two out of the Nine faculty members are Ph.D holders and the rest of the faculty members are pursuing their research. The department has produced quality professionals, holding important positions in Information Technology industry in India and abroad. Our notable alumni members have been excelling in key posts in various reputed organizations. Our students have also been pursuing research in reputed universities and institutions. The department conducts National seminars almost every year inviting eminent resource persons from the educational and industrial fields. The department is recognized as a Research Centre during 2018-19. In order to inculcate research and innovation in the field of computing, a special research room with lab is setup under the Department of Computer Science. Besides academic courses and soft skills training, research and innovations are given due importance. Remedial coaching to the weak students has improved the academic performance of weaker students.</p>
<h3 style="text-transform: uppercase;margin-left: 30px;color: rgb(21, 57, 214);">language</h3>
<p style="font-size:20px ;">Arabic, Malayalam and Hindi departments have been functioning since the inception of the college. These departments function as additional faculties to BA / BSc / BCom / B.Voc Degree courses. The faculty conducts various programmes to improve language skills of students. Dr. Haskerali E C, Head of Department of Malayalam Department has published two books titled ‘Mappila Vasantham’, and ‘Samskaravum Nagarikathayum’. Dr. Jabir Amani, Head of the Department of Arabic, has written and published four text books in Arabic, a book for B.A. Arabic (Afzal -Ul-Ulama) and B.Com II Semester, University of Calicut. He was awarded Ph.D in 2016.</p>
<h3 style="text-transform: uppercase;margin-left: 30px;color: rgb(93, 136, 25);">english </h3>
<p style="font-size:20px ;">The department has been functioning with a B A Programme since the inception of the college. The student intake is 40. The M.A. English Course began in 2003 with a student intake of 20. The department has Five permanent teachers and Six guest faculties.

    The department has organised several national and international seminars and symposia over the past few years. Two day National Seminar on Media and its Current Significations during November 2013, Two day National Seminar on Politics and Poetics of Representation in 2016 are a few to mention. The  International Coloquium on Creative Teaching and Learning in Higher Education organized between December 12-14,  was another prestigious event organized by the Department. Erudite Lecture by Prof. Gayatri Chakravorty Spivak, world renowned scholar, theorist and professor of English at Columbia University, was the major highlight of the three day colloquim. The department has a full-fledged Department Library and a Lecture Hall with public address system.</p>
<h3 style="text-transform: uppercase;margin-left: 30px;color: rgb(112, 14, 83);">statistics</h3>
<p style="font-size:20px ;">The department of Statistics started functioning since the inception of the college as a complimentary course of B.Sc Mathematics and B.Sc Computer Science</p>
