<p style="font-size:20px ;">Areekode is known for its fame in football as well as educational revolution.
    Hundreds of international, national, university, state, clubs and district football
    players hailed from this village on the bank of river Chaliyar. Establishment of a
    college in the year 1995 in this village has added further fuel for the development
    of Football as well as other sports activities in general in general.
    Department of Physical education started functioning since the
    inception of the college without much sports infrastructural facilities. But now
    within 25 years, the college has a Football stadium with gallery, indoor stadium,
    multipurpose court, badminton court, multi gym and table tennis hall.
    The college achieved medals and championships in international,
    national, state, university and district level competitions. The college produced</p>
<h3 style="text-transform: uppercase;margin-left: 30px;color: rgb(57, 26, 128);">maths</h3>
<p style="font-size:20px ;">FACULTY OF MATHEMATICS B.Sc Mathematics Course started since the inception of the college in 1995. The student intake is 48. The PG course was sanctioned in 2004 with 20 seats. The department includes three permanent staff and six guest lecturers. All the three permanent staff, Dr Sajith, Dr. Fazeela and Dr. Sameeha Rahmani have published papers in International and National journals. The department conducts Seminars and Workshops regularly</p>
<h3 style="text-transform: uppercase;margin-left: 30px;color: rgb(112, 114, 16);">physics</h3>
<p style="font-size:20px ;">  The department started with B.Sc course in 1999. The student intake is 40. The PG course started in 2004 and has 12 seats. The faculty includes four permanent teachers and 3 guest lecturers. Department maintains 100% result al-most every year. The students of the department win first prizes in the National Level Essay Presentation Contest prganized by BARC, Mumbai, almost every year. A material Sciences lab also been setup under the department for promoting research among students in this area. Department regularly organizes seminars and conferences and conducts Open House Programme as part of the Science Day Celebrations every year.  Dr. Mohemmed Shanid. N.A published 3 papers in international publications</p>
<h3 style="text-transform: uppercase;margin-left: 30px;color: rgb(28, 7, 34);">commerce</h3>
<p style="font-size:20px ;">COMMERCE The college started functioning in 1995 with undergraduate courses in arts and science. With the dawn of the academic year 2006-07, the college inaugurated the functioning of the department of Commerce under the self financing sector The student intake is 40. The department conducted a UGC sponsored National Venture Capital Summit-Sanaabil in January 2011. In 2014, the department strated M.Com Course in the aided sector The student intake is 20. In the acdemic year 2013-14, the department conducted two UGC sponsered National Seminars.</p>
<h3 style="text-transform: uppercase;margin-left: 30px;color: rgb(38, 97, 10);">economics</h3>
<p style="font-size:20px ;">The College started offering B.A. Economics in 2013 in the Self-financing sector. The student intake is 40. In 2014, Government of Kerala sanctioned BA Economics programme in the aided sector and college converted the existing programme from self-financing to aided sector. Since the Governement hasn't created any permanent teaching post in the department, appointment has been made on contract basis. Presently 3 full time teachers are working in the department.</p>
<h3 style="text-transform: uppercase;margin-left: 30px">broadcasting and journalism</h3>
<p style="font-size:20px ;">The college has started two B Voc degree programmes during the year 2014-15. Sanctioned by the University Grants Commission (UGC), this newly designed, novel graduate programme - Bachelor of Vocation programme - is a part of Commission’s effort to promote skill development based higher education, incorporating specific job rule under the National Skill Qualification Frame work (NSQF).

    Similar to conventional degree programmes, B.Voc follows the pattern of three year credit and semester system. But, unlike other graduate programmes, B.Voc offers multiple entry and exit options. Students who are completing the first year will be getting a diploma, and an advanced diploma after the second year and a degree certificate on completion of the entire three year programme.
    
    The department is offering a three year B.Voc Programme in Broadcasting & Journalism with an intake of 50 students. The College has created linkages and signed MoUs with various media organizations for the skill training of the students.</p>
